<h2 id="amphetamine">Amphetamine</h2>
<hr />
<p>This little utility stops your Mac from using its power saving features such as dimming the display or putting a hard drive to sleep. Useful if you have a task to complete that will take longer than the sleep mode of your Mac is set to.</p>

<p>Itâ€™s configurable allowing you to choose which hard drives to keep awake and how long it should run for and much more.</p>

<p><img src="https://grovetech.co/assets/img/blog/2018/top5/Amphetamine1280.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded m-2" width="750" /></p>
<h2 id="onyx">Onyx</h2>
<hr />
<p>If your Mac is slowing down Onyx offers to verify the startup disk and the structure of its system files, to run miscellaneous maintenance and cleaning tasks, to configure parameters in the Finder, Dock, Safari, and some of Appleâ€™s applications, to delete caches, to remove certain problematic folders and files, to rebuild various databases and indexes, and more.</p>

<p>All for free and from one easy to use interface, no need to delve into the Terminal to remove out of date caches Onyx can do that for you from a GUI.</p>

